com.mesosphere.sdk.offer.evaluate

Class ResourceEvaluationStage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mesosphere.sdk.offer.evaluate.ResourceEvaluationStage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OfferEvaluationStage
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PortEvaluationStage, VolumeEvaluationStage

    public class ResourceEvaluationStage
extends java.lang.Object
implements OfferEvaluationStage
    This class evaluates an offer against a given OfferRequirement, ensuring that it contains a sufficient amount or value of the supplied Resource, and creating a ReserveOfferRecommendation or UnreserveOfferRecommendation where necessary.

        public ResourceEvaluationStage(Resource resource,
                               java.lang.String taskName)
        Instantiate this class to check incoming offers for sufficient presence of the supplied Resource. The supplied task name indicates which task in the OfferRequirement to update with any subsequent metadata. If it is null, this stage will modify the org.apache.mesos.Protos.ExecutorInfo instead.
        Parameters:
        resource - the resource to evaluate incoming offers against
        taskName - the name of the task to modify with resource metadata

      • evaluate

        public EvaluationOutcome evaluate(MesosResourcePool mesosResourcePool,
                                  PodInfoBuilder podInfoBuilder)
        Description copied from interface: OfferEvaluationStage
        Evaluate the given offer (in the form of a MesosResourcePool, modifying the org.apache.mesos.Protos.TaskInfos and org.apache.mesos.Protos.ExecutorInfo in the given OfferRequirement where appropriate to ensure they have necessary metadata (e.g. a populated environment variable), deducting used resources from the pool, and creating the appropriate OfferRecommendation in the given OfferRecommendationSlate if relevant.
        Specified by:
        evaluate in interface OfferEvaluationStage
        Parameters:
        mesosResourcePool - the available resources left available for this stage to consume
        podInfoBuilder - the grouping of all task and executor builders for the pod
        Returns:
        an EvaluationOutcome describing whether this evaluation stage succeeded or failed, and why
